item.title: Ip change,
item.dc:creator: @Javac_Batch Javac Batch
item.description:
@Javac_Batch wrote:

EGUI.Java – Change “”, “”, “”, to your ip. So it would look like this - “example.no-ip.biz”, “example.no-ip.biz”, “example.no-ip.biz”

Then in Client.Java (Client files), change the current IP (whatever it’s set to) then put yours.

Tip - For users not to edit it make a copy of it for players then select each file by highlighting it EXCEPT RUN AND COMPILE then right click > Properties > And put a checkmark in the hidden box.

Google it for info on how to unhide.
